import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    data['year'] = data['date'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby(['year', 'month']).mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='month', y='temperature', hue='year', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['temperature'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Temperature: {:.2f}'.format(data['temperature'].mean()))
    chart.legend(loc='upper left')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of temperature throughout the year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['hour'] = data['hour'].astype(str)
    sns.boxplot(x='hour', y='wind', data=data)
    plt.title('How does wind speed vary with time of day?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['pressure'] = pd.to_numeric(data['pressure'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pressure', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].mean(), color='red', label=f'mean: {data["pressure"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].median(), color='green', label=f'median: {data["pressure"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of atmospheric pressure?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
